metadata.name: F.A.M(Future Art Makers)
metadata.description: F.A.M believe it or not created itself for the most part. I used an entire tube of uncut oil paint to soak the background. I then let it sit for a week and it formed the two taller objects by somewhat pooling in the middle. I spontaneously outlined and painted in the other Figures to somewhat make it come to where it is now. To me it was as if the piece knew what it wanted to become.
